ularly critical of a decision at the end of the 1990s to buy Comax, which had many short-term contracts with the Defence Evaluation Research Agency and which it has found difficulty having renewed.\"</p><p>But the relationship between the two remains. In June QinetiQ gave a &pound;200m contract for Amey to provide facilities management services for 30 of the QinetiQ sites. The technology company is expected to win a &pound;1bn price tag on flotation and Mr Love's 0.76% stake - bought for barely &pound;100,000 - is expected to grow to 1.8%, worth &pound;18m.</p>","headline":"Putting a price on privatisation","trailText":"<p><strong>Profile:</strong> Graham Love, the new chief executive of QinetiQ.</p>","newspaperPageNumber":"23","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"The Guardian","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/9b58","wordcount":"306","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"5295941","allowUgc":"false","isPremoderated":"false","internalPageCode":"185309","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2005/sep/28/Whitehall.politics1","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/business/2005/sep/28/Whitehall.politics1","tags":[{"id":"business/business","webTitle":"Business","type":"keyword","sectionId":"business","sectionName":"Business","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/business/business","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/business/business","references":[]},{"id":"politics/civil-service","webTitle":"Civil service","type":"keyword","sectionId":"politics","sectionName":"Politics","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/politics/civil-service","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/politics/civil-service","references":[]},{"id":"politics/politics","webTitle":"Politics","type":"keyword","sectionId":"politics","sectionName":"Politics","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/politics/politics","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/politics/politics","references